text: This is the home you have been waiting for! Four bedroom home with soaring ceilings and plenty of space to call your own. The location can't be beat! Across the street from a trail that takes you right down to the beach and shopping in just a few minute walk. Home also sits on a lot that backs a vacant drainage lot so there are no, and never will be, neighbors behind this gorgeous home. Main level features formal living and dining rooms and family room is open to the large kitchen. Huge laundry room leaves lots of room for storage. Upstairs has 4 nice sized bedrooms. Primary suite has huge bathroom with separate shower and tub and large walk in closet. A fully fenced dog run can be found through the dog door in the laundry room.

Beautiful like-new home, built in 2019 w/ many upgrades. The open great room concept welcomes you in with vaulted ceilings, cozy gas fireplace & hard surface floors thru the entry, great room, kitchen & dining area. The light, bright & very open kitchen design has self-closing slide out drawers, a full size pantry cabinet, island sink and all upgraded LG appliances stay! (yes, even the Washer/Dryer stay). The main floor Primary bedroom's MASSIVE walk-in closet & storage cubby are HUGE, and the walk-in tile shower is impressive. Upper floor has (2) additional bedrooms, a full bath plus a bonus room! All this in an affordable gated community for privacy & security. Lot backs to an Open Space Tract too!

Welcome to your dream home in Bellingham's coveted Columbia neighborhood. This meticulously remodeled gem offers 2 bedrooms, 1.5 baths, and an inviting open living space, perfect for modern in town living. Step outside to your own private oasis, complete with a thoughtfully landscaped fenced yard, fire ring, gazebo with hot tub, as well as a covered BBQ patio. Garden enthusiasts take note of the front garden beds! One car garage/shop with tons of built in storage, and two private off street parking pads provide room for everything. Walk to parks, shops the waterfront and more! What more could you dream of? This beauty will not last long!

Step up to affordable living in the heart of Sudden Valley with this charming, well-maintained single-level home. Featuring an open-concept design and vaulted ceilings throughout, the free-standing propane fireplace adds a cozy, cabin-in-the-woods ambiance. Perched on a hillside, the large wrap-around deck offers a perfect spot to soak in the peaceful setting. The home includes ample storage space below the living room and sits on an oversized lot, presenting numerous expansion opportunities. Enjoy the abundant community amenities and the convenience of being just minutes from Bellingham. Discover the perfect blend of comfort, potential, and natural beauty in this inviting home.

You will love the curb appeal & everything about this easy living one level home. It features include central air conditioning, manicured yard with sprinkler system, spacious covered patio for outside enjoyment complete with beautiful water features & views of the pond. The interior of the home is in move in condition. It has an open & airy feeling with high ceilings & an open concept living. The spacious living room is open to the informal dining area and kitchen. It also has an formal dining room which could easily be used as an office. The kitchen features lots of cabinets, hard surface counters with nice appliances. The primary suite is spacious with a corner fireplace and great sized walk in closet. You won't want to miss this one.

Welcome home to Festival Square, one of Bellingham's most desirable 55+ condominium communities. This rarely available, easily accessible ground-level 1, 038 sq ft, 2 bed/1.75 bath unit enjoys a peaceful location at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac. Sunny, west-facing windows and deck overlook a serene 15-acre protected nature preserve with a spring-fed pond, home to Bald Eagles, Herons, and songbirds. Affordable HOA dues include Water/Sewer/Garbage/Cable/lawn service and more. Financially healthy Association with well-maintained buildings. Clubhouse on property. Pet's allowed (some restrictions). Great central location in Cordata close to medical, shopping, services, parks, and miles of trails. ADU accessible, no steps.

Here is what you have been looking for! A well appointed single level home in Barkley Meadows! Walk to Barkley Village, the movie theater, Sunset Square or Lowe's! The vaulted ceilings and well planned layout make this home feel larger than it's square footage. Come in and see the new granite countertops, stainless steel sink, and new kitchen faucet. Also rest assured that you'll always be warm as the furnace was replaced in 2022 and to deal with Bellingham's hottest days know that there is a 2023 installed heat pump that will provide air conditioning. The washer and dryer, which convey, are also brand new! Walking distance to Bellingham's Railroad trail to take you anywhere you want to go by bike or foot.

This cozy, stylish Home is 3 bd 2 Bath situated on almost 5 acres and is offering tons of space for hobbies or work with the spacious shops and detached garage! Oversized 3-bay shop is connected to its own electrical meter making it perfect for personal use or to lease out for additional income! Detached 2 car garage with loft and carport perfect for your boat or camper! Endless opportunities in developing this beautiful piece of land with the potential to build your dream home on the back half of the property. Enjoy all the area has to offer with the State Park, boat launch, and grocery stores all close by! Not to mention that Grandview is the driest road in the winter!! 20 min. to Bellingham. And 15 Minutes to Canadian border.

Welcome to this inviting home nestled in the sought-after Whatcom Falls neighborhood. Featuring 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and a spacious bonus room/4th bedroom, this residence offers flexibility to accommodate diverse needs. Relax in the cozy living room, anchored by a gas fireplace and flooded with natural light from the massive windows. Situated on a 10K SF lot, the property boasts a lush backyard with mature trees and shrubs, perfect private dinners on the deck. Positioned towards the rear of the lot, the home provides ample front yard space with plenty of parking, including covered space for an RV. Enjoy the convenience of walking to Lake Whatcom + Whatcom Falls Park, or take a short drive to Galbraith Trails, Whole Foods, or downtown.

Discover privacy and tranquility in this 5-acre park-like setting. View kaleidoscopic sunsets and partial Bay, Island and Olympic Mountain views. Pacific Northwest craftsmanship includes wood beams, custom woodworking and main- level living. Enjoy energy efficiency with solar panels on the shop, a heat pump, solar water and radiant floor heating. An expansive 3-bay shop with RV parking and 1/2 bath allows for vehicle storage, woodworking and hobbies. Exercise year round in the commercial-grade indoor pool surrounded by glass sliders. Gardeners will covet the fenced garden with fruit trees, grape vines, berries and newly planted vegetable beds. All within minutes to downtown Bellingham, Barkley Village, shopping and amenities.

Welcome to a warm and inviting single-level haven, nestled within the heart of a picturesque small town. With 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, this newer construction home embraces you with its open-concept living space and custom fireplace, offering moments of relaxation. The kitchen, a masterpiece of design, beckons you to create memorable gatherings and culinary delights, while the covered deck invites you to unwind amidst captivating mountain views. Embrace the serenity of the expansive lot, where nature's beauty surrounds you, creating the perfect backdrop for treasured moments. Located just steps from the Canadian border and a short 40-mile drive to the renowned Mt. Baker ski resort, indulge in the allure of convenience and natural beauty.

Unique Opportunity to enjoy Coastal living in a dream location with partial ocean views and a 5 min walk to the beach! This 2 bedroom, 1 bath home is located on a quiet Cul-de-sac and on a spacious lot backing on to a green space. Vaulted ceilings and large sun filled windows make the interior bright and inviting. Extra Large Patio with plenty of room for outdoor dining, sunny days and relaxing evenings. Separate spacious laundry room with sink and plenty of storage. Brand new roof, gutters, down spouts and skylights installed in March 2024.

Experience casual elegance in this modern designed home with green-belt at the rear & filtered views of Lake Whatcom and the Stewart Mountains from the front. First level has a large 2-car garage; half bathroom; and large laundry room. The 2nd level has a wonderful open design with Living Room, Kitchen (with island) & Dining Room. Rear patio area off of the Dining Room. The Kitchen has white cabinet package with light quartz countertops & stainless steel appliances. Elegant stone 'floor to ceiling' gas fireplace is a wonderful centerpiece in the Living Room. The office and another half bathroom completes the 2nd floor. Upstairs has the Primary Bedroom with onsuite bathroom and walk-in closet. Two other bedrooms & a full bath up.

Breathtaking mountain views from this gorgeous home in a secluded cul-de-sac. This spacious 5-bedroom sanctuary with tons of natural light boasts an additional bonus room, encompassing 4283 sqft of luxurious living space. Retreat to the primary bedroom oasis featuring a cozy fireplace & indulge in relaxation with the private bath complete with a lavish jetted tub. Entertain with ease in the elegant dining room enhanced by vaulted ceilings & skylights, creating an ambiance of sophistication & warmth. Around the corner you will find the wet bar, including sink, fridge, & storage, a welcome addition to any entertaining space. Unwind in the sauna or gather around the fireplace. This home is the epitome of comfort & luxury-living at its finest!

This beautiful Cornwall Park home is located just steps from Broadway Park. Well maintained and extensively remodeled, this home retains its period charm. Completely updated bathrooms and kitchen, new paint inside and out, and freshly refinished hardwood floors are just the beginning. The classic custom built-ins and original front door have been restored to their original classic look, showing off the custom tilework surrounding the fireplace. Primary bedroom on the main level has cedar-lined closet. Large bedrooms with walk in closets upstairs. Large walkout basement space for workshop or storage. Fully fenced back yard and detached garage off the quiet alley behind. Close to downtown, waterfront, and all the best Bellingham has to offer.
neighborhoods: Broadway Park Historic District, Cornwall Park

text: Nestled beside a tranquil creek, this captivating home offers a harmonious blend of serenity and convenience. With a spacious two-car garage and three inviting bedrooms, it combines practicality with comfort. Discover the joy of nearby shopping amenities while unwinding on your private patio, embraced by the soothing sounds of nature. Your pet will adore the dedicated fenced area, while you gather around the fire pit for enchanting evenings under the stars. Delight in the modern comforts of central AC, sprinklers, and stainless steel appliances, including a new fridge. Lots of sunlight through the ample windows, infusing the main living room with warmth and brightness. Come home to a haven where tranquility meets modern convenience.

Beautifully updated Fairhaven Square Condo! Light & bright open-concept floor plan w/ soaring ceilings, new LVP flooring, & charming Juliet balcony w/ French doors & west-facing sunset views. Designer kitchen w/ SS appliances, breakfast bar & modern sink w/ built-in cutting board attachment. Dedicated dining area, office nook, & sunny living room w/ balcony access. Light-filled primary suite w/ walk-in closet & large windows, full bathroom w/ updated tile flooring. New light fixtures/ceiling fan & fresh paint throughout! In-unit Washer/Dryer. Shared rooftop deck, gated garage parking w/ designated space, secure building entry, & located in the heart of Fairhaven near Boulevard Park, Interurban Trail & Fairhaven Village Green. Welcome Home!

Custom designed rambler built in 2017 by Pioneer Post Frame with metal siding and roof makes for easy care living on this tree lined 10 acres providing ultimate privacy. The open floor plan with vaulted ceilings and two sets of French doors floods the home with light and walk out to the covered wrap around porch to relax and enjoy your private oasis. Easy care vinyl plank floors and carpet in the bedrooms with radiant floor heat and freestanding wood stove is nice and cozy. The large primary bedroom with an ensuite bath. The level and sunny acreage has a large garden and fruit trees. The storage container shop with covered carport. Not on leased land. The RR5A zoning allows property to be subdivided (buyer to verify). Close to the bay.
nearby_schools: Ferndale School District, Lummi Elementary School, Lummi High School

text: Welcome to this updated mid-century style home w/ a detached guest house and garage! Situated on a picturesque private acre, minutes to Gailbraith, parks, trails & town. Unique low maintenance, live edge cedar siding. Inside, 2 granite fireplaces - living room & kitchen, cathedral ceilings & stunning line of vertical windows bringing nature in. Newer LVP flooring & carpet. An updated kitchen w/ stainless steel appliances & eco-friendly PaperStone counters. The primary suite w/ large walk-in shower, closets galore & an adjacent office/nursery. French doors lead to a large patio, then on to a charming guest house with full kitchen, washer/dryer, walk-in closet, Victorian style bath & a cottage garden. Guests? Income? Yes, all of it!

New construction! Est completion May 30. This brand new 3 bed, 1.75 bath is located in a serene setting, with the back of house facing a beautiful woodland scene and view of Kendall Lake. The vaulted ceilings create a light and airy feel inside. Kitchen and bathrooms are outfitted with quartz countertops. The primary bedroom has an attached en-suite with shower, while the full bathroom with shower and tub is accessible to the rest of the house. The exterior insulation has been upgraded beyond the building code requirements for better home temperature efficiency and noise dampening. Additionally, the interior walls have been insulated for noise dampening between rooms. The house is a blank canvas waiting for you to make it home!
Nice 10K + sq ft corner lot ready for you to build on.

Great opportunity to own a classic, water-view, downtown Blaine home with rare, mixed-use zoning! Located less than 1 mile from the Canadian border with easy access to I-5. Walking distance to the growing and vibrant downtown Blaine scene. Mature landscaping and a wrap-around front porch are perfect for watching beautiful sunsets over the marina as well as the 4th of July parade. This home is zoned for either residential, commercial, or both. It would make a great home-office. It has been used in the past as a primary residence, a residential and commercial rental, a real estate office, law office, and accounting office. Listed as 2 bd. With garage, easily could be 3 or 4 bd. Possibilities are endless.

Welcome home to this nearly new 2 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom home, with 1, 537 sq. ft. with an oversized garage. Floor plan is designed to make the most of the sunny, western exposure. Upon entering the main floor, you will discover a bedroom and an additional bonus room that can serve as an office, TV area, or occasional guest space. The upper level houses the great room and primary bedroom, along with a covered deck that offers views of stunning sunsets. The kitchen boasts quartz countertops, modern cabinets with undermount lighting. Conveniently located near shopping, restaurants, the downtown waterfront and marina, parks, trails, mini golf and easy I5 and border access as well.

Welcome to your dream retreat overlooking Lummi Bay & the San Juan Islands! This meticulously remodeled 3 bed/2 bath home boasts a long list of top-of-the-line upgrades including: New plumbing & electrical, 100% waterproof LVP flooring, & Arte wallcoverings from Belgium. Smart home features include Emtek keyless entry, Nest thermostat, Arlo security cameras, & Lutron lighting. The chef's kitchen features Jenn Air appliances, quartz countertops, & custom cabinetry. Relax in the living room by your linear fireplace or retreat through the double sliding doors to your expansive Trex deck. The combination butler pantry/laundry room provides an abundance of space, storage & functionality. This home is the definition of turnkey. Don't miss out!
nearby_schools: Ferndale School District, Lummi Elementary School, Lummi High School

text: Beautifully updated 3bd/1ba single level home in the heart of Bellingham. Located on a quiet street blocks from Whatcom Falls and walking distance to Barkley Village & Roosevelt Elementary. This home has been completely renovated including: fully remodeled bathroom w/ low step-in tiled shower, new sewer line, hot water tank, upgraded kitchen w/granite counters, new flooring, interior and exterior paint, convection heaters and a 4yo roof w/new leafguard gutters. Living room opens onto a large covered deck & a meticulously landscaped backyard which is fully fenced. 2 Car garage w/ built in shelving & a separate fully insulated shop/storage area is attached to the home. Don't miss out on the perfect opportunity to own a move in ready home.

Discover the potential of this tranquil, level one-acre secluded property w/a 2 bed mobile home and large shop. Ideal for those seeking privacy, you can renovate the current structures or tear down and build your dream home. Utilities are ready with a septic system and well water in place. Conveniently located just 20 minutes from Bellingham, close to Mt. Baker and the Nooksack River, and only minutes to the post office and grocery store. Whether you're an investor or looking for a private oasis, this estate sale offers endless possibilities for your vision.

Experience the epitome of tranquility in this secluded Sudden Valley sanctuary, nestled on a private double lot. A horticultural haven awaits, boasting fenced in vegetable patches and natural landscapes, supported by a storage shed and fire pit. Entertain effortlessly in the cozy living room with gas fireplace that accesses the three-tiered deck, all enclosed within a fully fenced backyard. Inside, panoramic windows frame breathtaking Pacific Northwest vistas, while the kitchen dazzles with granite tile counters, and abundant storage. Recent upgrades include laminate floors, roof, crawlspace encapsulation, refrigerator and heat pump. Close access to a private marina, kayak launch, premier golf course, gym, sauna, swimming pools and trails.

Presenting Salmonberry #206! This modern studio boasts high-end finishes like SS appliances, quartz countertops, & designer cabinetry. Luxury vinyl plank flooring combines durability with elegance. Complete with in-unit W/D, 2 storage closets, & ample natural light, all essentials are covered. Accessible via stairs or a ramp for a no-step entry, this 2nd-floor unit offers convenience for all. Nestled in the heart of Lynden, enjoy easy access to amenities. Yet, what truly distinguishes this unit are the serene surroundings. Open the door to reveal breathtaking views of Fishtrap Creek, lush trees & distant mountains. FHA approved, rental cap not exceeded. Ideal for first-time homeowners or savvy investors. Don't miss out on this opportunity!

Welcome to 202 E Wiser Lake Rd! This 1/2 acre lot is the perfect place to build your dream home and have plenty of room for a shop or outbuildings. Great sandy soil and no wetlands makes for a simple septic and basement options, water share included! Fantastic location on Wiser Lake Rd just East of the Guide Meridian means you're 5 mins from Lynden and 15 mins from Bellingham! Amazing opportunity for one of the few remaining lots in this area.

Charming 3 bedroom / 2 bath rambler is nestled in a quiet setting in the Whatcom Falls neighborhood. This is a mountain biker or hiker's dream location, just a short pedal from the world class Galbraith Mountain trail system. Freshly painted kitchen with new induction range and microwave. Cozy wood burning fireplace in living room. Attached double garage. Two storage sheds. The extra deep yard is very private and fully fenced, backing with a gate onto the Kulshan Middle School playfield. Relax on the partially covered patio and enjoy the peaceful sounds of birds in the trees. There is plenty of room for gardening, dogs, or possibly a detached ADU. Pre-inspection report is available. A very rare find at this price point. Don't miss this one!

A stunning home in the heart of the Geneva neighborhood. Close to trails, Lake Whatcom and direct access to Galbraith, this home is the epitome of Bellingham living. Sitting on a dead-end cul-de-sac you have privacy while also being immersed in a quiet community. Walk in to a cozy and unique layout that includes a beautiful atrium ready to be adorned with house plants. Open and airy, the layout lends itself to endless possibilities. Enjoy the convenience of an attached garage, off-street parking, and a covered back deck for outdoor relaxation. Several recent updates include a new roof and wood stove. Dont miss the opportunity to make this gem your new home and personal retreat!

Gracious country living with elegant style and gardens awaiting your touch! Stunning contemporary kitchen; gorgeous granite countertops. Statement rock fireplace highlights the luxurious great room. Well-cared-for, truly unique country property, with 3 bedrooms/2 baths. Vaulted ceilings breathe comfort into flowing architectural plan, which wisely uses every angle of nearly 1, 600 sq.ft. Backyard of your dreams, with raised beds and huge (hidden) chicken coop; producing fruit trees, Asian pears, berries. BBQ patio area; coordinated walkways, paths through quiet gardens. Enthusiastic birders and outdoor fans can love this place! Clean & tidy, organized & practical, yet its casual outdoor theme allows creative options. An impressive PNW value!

What an incredible opportunity for home ownership in Bellingham! Perfect for a first-time home buyer or anyone looking for the ideal spot. 2 Beds, & 2 baths with a lovely living area where you can sit by the fireplace & read a good book. There's no age restriction, & this is a stand-alone home featuring a 1 car garage & a perfect backyard to garden or allow pets to play. Cook or host guests in the modern kitchen boasting granite countertops & stainless steel appliances. Additional features: This house backs up to a walking trail. Newer home built by Grandview Homes. Also includes a deck, hardwood floors, custom cabinets and a custom German-made fridge to fit the space perfectly. Close to everything Bellingham has to offer!

Welcome to Whispering Meadows. Immaculate new construction home in one of the newest developments in Nooksack. This 3 bed/1.75 bath has it all. As you walk through the front door you'll notice how open & spacious this floor plan is with the vaulted ceilings throughout the kitchen, dining & living room. Kitchen features soft close cabinets, a large island with seating, quartz countertops, Stainless Steel appliances. Enjoy the huge back yard & the amazing views of the mountains off in the distance. Primary bedroom features vaulted ceilings, walk-in shower, double vanity, & a huge walk-in closet. Ductless mini splits to keep you cool in the summer & warm in the winter. All of this within walking distance to Nooksack Elementary & Middle School.

Nestled at the bottom of Alabama Hill sits this single-story home with close proximity to the trails, Lake Whatcom, and Barkley Village. Seller has recently updated the home with white cabinetry in the kitchen, luxury vinyl planking throughout and composition roof in 2020. The floorplan flows well with a generous living area, dining space and galley kitchen. The primary bedroom features an ensuite 3/4 bathroom, the secondary bedrooms share a full main bath off the hallway. Outside, the fully fenced back yard provides lots of space to enjoy the sunshine or host a summer BBQ. The shed in the back yard conveys, and if you need more space for storage - the two car garage has you covered. Check out this fantastic home today!

This impressive custom-designed Craftsman spans 3 levels~5 bed/5 ba w/primary on the main. Appreciate custom touches as you enter dbl doors~ vaulted wood lined ceilings & gas FP for a remarkable ambiance. This residence promises endless opportunities for relaxation & entertainment-includes a theatre rm w/surround sound-5 mounted TVs are included! Above the newly added 2nd garage, a pvt entrance offers a spacious office/bonus space w/ 1/2 ba + wet bar. Natural light pours in through skylights, complemented by a mini-split system. Covered patio w/spa & gas BBQ hookup, perfect for outdoor gatherings. Enjoy active leisure; sports court features LED lights+Bluetooth speakers. Sprinklers maintain the lush yard, invisible fence ensures pet safety.

Enjoy your large, private feeling beautiful lot with a very well maintained spacious 5th wheel. This is a great start property, offering everything you need, with room to add your personal touches. Sit on the deck and enjoy the natural setting, or be active at one of the many great amenities the Glen has to offer. The Glen is zoned recreational for 120 days of use out of the year and has all the amenities you could want, including 2 pools, hot tub, tennis court, library, laundry mat, 2 clubhouse, 24 hr security, gated entry, & play areas.

Step onto your own private oasis in division three. Lush greenspace gives you privacy and a beautiful view as you sit around the campfire, or on the large covered deck. Inside boasts a large loft, plenty of storage, and lots of windows to allow in natural light. Also included on the property is a shed for additional or larger storage items. This is truly a relaxing home away from home!The Glen is zoned recreational for 120 days of use out of the year and has all the amenities you could want, including 2 pools, hot tub, tennis court, library, laundry mat, 2 clubhouse, 24 hr security, gated entry, & play areas.

Embrace the potential of this spacious 4 bedroom 2.5 bath home nestled on a serene wooded corner lot in Edgmoor's Hidden Hills neighborhood. This property offers ample space for comfortable living with a generous tri-level floor plan. Surrounded by mature trees, the tranquil setting provides privacy and a connection to nature. With cosmetic upgrades, the home presents a remarkable opportunity to create your dream residence in an enviable location.

Discover this one-level home nestled in a private location in a quiet neighborhood, featuring 3 bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms with an open floor plan. The private, fully fenced backyard boasts apple and plum trees, beautiful flowers, and ample garden space. Inside, the spacious kitchen is equipped with granite countertops, a tile backsplash, and stainless steel appliances. Highlights include a custom blind package, a welcoming front patio, and superb landscaping, all combining to offer comfort and charm.

Welcome to River-Walk, a unique NW Washington community offering attractive design, luxurious finishes, beautiful views & pedestrian-friendly connectivity to Lynden. Walk or bike a few blocks to downtown to Lyndens quaint restaurants & stores. River-Walk is less than 2 hours to Seattle, Vancouver, B.C., Mt. Baker & the San Juan Islands. Lot 8 is in River-Walks west side, reserved for 55+ active adults w/ tech features including high-speed fiber optic cable. It offers a comfortable 2013sqft w/ 3 beds & 2.25 baths. The gourmet kitchen is highlighted by quartz countertops & islands w/ waterfall drops. Direct GPS to 202 Riverview Road, Lynden. Builders modified floor plan to increase upper loft area - price increase reflects changes.
